    "description": "CyberBuzz, Inc. engages in the advertising and marketing activities in Japan. The company offers NINARY, a membership service that requires the approval of people who are especially influential on social media; Ripre, that allows to create product experiences and impressions on SNS and word-of-mouth sites; and Be One Agent, that provides valuable solutions to advertisers and creators. It also provides Owgi, a one-stop SNS operation management tool; BRIDGE, a SNS account management agency service that support planning, creative production, posting, and effectiveness measurement; DETEKURU, a matching service that connects companies and creators specializing in user-generated content; HR business that provides job change support for SNS marketing personnel; and WithLIVE, a live distribution platform where artists and users can talk online. In addition, the company offers To Buy, a media outlet for short movies; TateLab, creative research for vertical short videos; as well as Casfeed, a casting tool for vertical short videos, and social media advertising optimization. CyberBuzz, Inc. was incorporated in 2006 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan."
